    "Fitting procedure for the gravity modelIn order to fit the gravity model, we used a linear regression of log-transformed variables.For each resolution level, we first computed for each year starting in 1997 the number of jumps between a source cell i and a target cell j (with i = j) and number of articles published in each cell in the 5 preceding years.",
    "The resolution of 1 year is a sweet spot between the typical inter-article time of a researcher (0.53 years) and the characteristic time at which researchers switch major topics (1.5 years, see Fig.",
